parameters.name: From
parameters.description:
The beginning of the time range to query. The value must be a unix timestamp. For example, 1600738962 specifies 09:42:42 (UTC+8) on September 22, 2020.

>  If you specify **From**, you must also specify **To** or **MinutePeriod**.

parameters.name: MinutePeriod
parameters.description:
The interval at which log data is queried. Unit: minutes.

>  If both **From** and **To** are not specified, you must specify **MinutePeriod**.

parameters.name: PageNumber
parameters.description: The number of the page to return. Default value: **1**.

parameters.name: PageSize
parameters.description: The number of entries to return on each page. Maximum value: **50**. Default value: **10**.

parameters.name: RegionId
parameters.description: The ID of the region where the SSL server is created. You can call the [DescribeRegions](~~36063~~) operation to query the most recent region list.

parameters.name: SslVpnClientCertId
parameters.description: The ID of the SSL client certificate.

parameters.name: To
parameters.description:
The end of the time range to query. The value must be a unix timestamp. For example, 1600738962 specifies 09:42:42 (UTC+8) on September 22, 2020.

>  If you specify **To**, you must also specify **From** or **MinutePeriod**.

parameters.name: VpnSslServerId
parameters.description: The ID of the SSL server.
